<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Deface" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Deface,</orth> 1) to disfigure, to soil: <bibl n="shak. luc 719" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 719</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 6.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 6, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 4.64.1" default="NO" valid="yes">64, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. pp 90" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 90</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.4.60" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 4, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.3.45" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 3, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.5.29" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.1.42" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 1, 42</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.1.122" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 1, 122</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.126" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 7, 126</bibl>.<lb />2) to blot, to obliterate: <cit><quote>pay him six thousand, and d. the bond,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 3.2.301" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 2, 301</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>blotting your names from books of memory, razing the characters of your renown, --ing monuments of conquered France,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.102" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 102</bibl></cit>. Perhaps also in <bibl n="shak. r3 2.1.122" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 1, 122</bibl>; but cf. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.4.60" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 4, 60</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>